\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Maximum New Edges:
\f1\b0  The new transaction requesting an exclusive (X) lock could be blocked by 
\f0\b all existing 'n' transactions
\f1\b0 .\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Reasoning:
\f1\b0 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl1\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 X-locks are not compatible with either S-locks or other X-locks.\
\ls3\ilvl1\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u9702 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 If any of the 'n' transactions holds either an S-lock or an X-lock on the object, the new transaction will have to wait, creating a new edge for each.\
